    narr:narration """This hub collects the canonical vocabulary of the pitch for [collective memory](narr:StyleObs_keyphrase_1) — the anchor term, repeated 20+ times and explicitly distinguished from individual AI memory. The product positioning clusters around [intellectual property as code](narr:Observation_IPAsCode) / [IP-as-code](narr:StyleObs_IPAsCode) (15+ uses), [narrative source of truth](narr:StyleObs_StockPhrase_1), [narrative architecture](narr:StyleObs_KeyPhrase_NarrArch), and git-parallel coinages like [witness repository](narr:StyleObs_7). The problem framing is vivid: [state secrets to AI](narr:Observation_StateSecrets), the [AI-context rich vs poor](narr:KeyPhrase_AIContextRich) divide, the [strategy-execution disconnect](narr:KeyPhrase_StrategyExecutionGap) \"[amount] mistake,\" and the flat [\"you can't\"](narr:KeyPhrase_YouCant) impossibility. Movement language sets [single-player vs multiplayer](narr:Observation_MultiplayerShift) and [intentional memory](narr:Observation_IntentionalMemory) against autosummarization. Metaphors run [steering wheel / backdoor / fault lines](narr:StyleObs_Metaphor_Steering), [steering vector](narr:StyleObs_Metaphor_Vector), and [deepest lever](narr:Observation_DeepestLever). Beneath the brand terms sits an internal technical layer — [Memory](narr:Obs_MemoryDefinition), [Transaction](narr:Obs_TransactionDefinition), [tool signatures and ontology](narr:StyleObs_TechTerms) — plus speculative coinages and two distinct pitch voices.""" ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/ns/narrative#KeyPhrase_1> ;
